## ðŸ“Š Key SQL Queries
1. **Overall Cancellation Rate**  
```sql
SELECT 
    COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
    SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS cancelled_orders,
    ROUND(100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*), 2) AS cancellation_rate
FROM orders;
Cancellations by Category

sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
    category,
    COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
    SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS cancelled_orders,
    ROUND(100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*), 2) AS cancellation_rate
FROM orders
GROUP BY category
ORDER BY cancellation_rate DESC;
Cancellations by Payment Method

sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
    payment_method,
    COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
    SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS cancelled_orders,
    ROUND(100.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(*), 2) AS cancellation_rate
FROM orders
GROUP BY payment_method
ORDER BY cancellation_rate DESC;
Monthly Cancellation Trends

sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
    strftime('%Y-%m', order_date) AS month,   -- use DATE_FORMAT(order_date, '%Y-%m') in MySQL
    COUNT(*) AS total_orders,
    SUM(CASE WHEN order_status = 'Cancelled' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS cancelled_orders
FROM orders
GROUP BY month
ORDER BY month;
